paragraph.content: Notes Recorded by Doctor, R. R, MD on 6/30/2014 at 2:08 PM
Mr. Doe,
Thank you for remembering to complete your labs. Your results explained below.
Electrolytes (sodium, potassium, chloride, CO2): normal
Creatinine: measure of kidney function, normal
A1C: screening test for diabetes, normal

Lipids: triglycerides are normal, HDL (good cholesterol) is normal at 51, LDL (bad cholesterol) is mildly elevated at 150. The LDL is not yet to a point that we would advise a medication. Continue to work on weight loss, increasing exercise. Avoid high cholesterol foods like butter, fried foods, red meat.
R. R Doctor, MD
